# Architecture plan for Issue #127: Move chat padding from list wrappers into each message card

## Module structure, file organization, shared types
- `frontend/src/styles.css` owns the Tailwind component-layer styles for the chat panel, message list, combined feed, and individual message cards. This issue should be implemented there.
- `frontend/src/App.tsx` renders the unified feed markup, but no React state, data flow, routing, or accessibility changes are needed for this visual spacing adjustment.
- `shared/src/*`, `backend/src/*`, and database migrations are out of scope because the issue does not change API contracts, persistence, or message models.

## Dependencies between issues
- Issue #127 has no blocking dependencies and can be implemented independently.
- It follows the previous feed-spacing changes from Issues 5.12 / 5.13, changing the spacing strategy from wrapper-side padding to message-card padding.

## Key design decisions
- Remove outer horizontal padding around the message list so cards can span the available feed width: set `.tlhn-chat-panel` horizontal padding to `px-0` while preserving vertical spacing, and set `.tlhn-chat-list-combined` to `pr-0`.
- Add inner padding directly to each `.tlhn-chat-message` (`px-3 py-2`, or `px-4 py-2` if the existing visual rhythm needs more room) so message text and metadata do not sit against the card border.
- Preserve the existing feed ordering, scroll behavior, faction colors, avatars, timestamps, and TLHN visual language.
- Validate with the frontend/shared build and, when available, the full workspace build.
